commit.message:
image: Fix video thumbnails

For the longest time this has been an issue, but would only cause
crashes on Windows so I thought it was just a gstreamer bug on Windows -
when it was actually the thumbnail data being freed because
Gdk::Pixbuf::create_from_data doesn't copy the data.

Also added the large thumbnails directory as a directory to get
thumbanils from, although normal will be searched first.

verification.payload:
tree 64d4964580fff096ac43fec7f3209f933942796b
parent 34583347c9bf35468d4e1f3c4becbb28d10a9836

commit.message:
imagebox: Prefer hardware accelerated video decoders

The only downside that I have noticed with this is that some invalid or
malformed files that play fine with the libgstlibav plugin do not work
with the nvcodec plugin.  I looked and I couldn't find a way to modify
the pipeline on the fly to try a different decoder when one fails.

Don't attempt to use xvimagesink or ximagesink when using a rgba visual
- they don't work with it.

This commit also changes the default X11/Wayland sink to a gtkglsink.

verification.payload:
tree 8d95238e79ecdec0c13b9ce4b4d2e231d0cbcb51
parent b762e7e3babeb2e758ac0c407796642d476157d1
author ahoka <ahodesuka@users.noreply.github.com> 1624340085 -0500
committer ahoka <ahodesuka@users.noreply.github.com> 1624340803 -0500

imagebox: Prefer hardware accelerated video decoders

The only downside that I have noticed with this is that some invalid or
malformed files that play fine with the libgstlibav plugin do not work

Don't attempt to use xvimagesink or ximagesink when using a rgba visual

This commit also changes the default X11/Wayland sink to a gtkglsink.

commit.message:
Rework initial image setting for local image lists

This cleans up some of the spaghetti when loading local imagelists,
and allows for the imagebox to determine by itself where it should draw.

update_widgets_visibility should always be called before the imagebox
draws so it can get the correct allocation before hand.
